From: Bryce Thomas <brycesub@gmail.com>
Subject: WaylandBackend: forward wl_touch input from the host compositor

The nested Wayland backend wired up pointer and keyboard input but
never requested wl_touch from the seat, so touchscreens were dead when
gamescope runs nested. Add a wl_touch listener on the input thread and
translate events to wlserver touch input, mirroring the SDL backend.

--- a/src/Backends/WaylandBackend.cpp
+++ b/src/Backends/WaylandBackend.cpp
@@ -593,6 +593,16 @@
 
